Nigeria Closes Amnesty for Niger Delta Militants, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-21T08:13:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/nigeria-closes-amnesty-for-niger-delta-militants-vanguard-says.html
A Nigerian government amnesty for
militants in the oil-rich Niger River delta  has ended , Vanguard
newspaper reported, citing Kingsley Kuku, a presidential adviser
on the region.  More than 26,000 fighters were pardoned under the program
since it started in 2009, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 